data.enText: to make sth continue at the same level, standard, etc.

data.chText: 维持治安；保持水平 / 平衡
data.enText: to maintain law and order/standards/a balance

data.chText: 这两个国家一直保持着密切关系。
data.enText: The two countries have always maintained close relations.

data.chText: 她一言不发，以保持尊严。

data.enText: to maintain prices (= prevent them falling or rising)
to keep a building, a machine, etc. in good condition by checking or repairing it regularly
The house is large and difficult to maintain.
to keep stating that sth is true, even though other people do not agree or do not believe it

data.chText: 这几个男人坚持说案发时他们在国外。
data.enText: The men maintained (that) they were out of the country when the crime was committed.

data.chText: 她一直坚持说她是无辜的。
data.enText: She has always maintained her innocence .
to support sb/sth over a long period of time by giving money, paying for food, etc.

data.chText: 她的收入养活一个孩子几乎都不够，更不用说三个了。
data.enText: Her income was barely enough to maintain one child, let alone three.

simple_means.memory_skill: main 逗留 + tain 拿 → 拿住，留住 → 维持

ex.chText: 哪家公司负责维护这台设备？
ex.enText: Which company is responsible for maintaining this equipment?

ex.chText: 这个花园很大，难以养护。
ex.enText: The garden is large and difficult to maintain.

synonyms.bx: 指经常维修机器、建筑物等，使其保持良好状态。

ex.chText: 我们必须为后代子孙保护土地/自然资源。
ex.enText: We must conserve our land/natural resources for future generations.

ex.chText: 一些环保人士呼吁政府采取有效措施保护野生动物。
ex.enText: Some environmentalists urged that the government take effective measures to conserve the wildlife.

synonyms.bx: 较正式用词，通常指保护自然资源使其不发生改变或破坏。

ex.chText: 市政委员会花了不少钱来保护那座古城堡。
ex.enText: The city council spent a lot of money to preserve the old castle.

ex.chText: 这个碗保存得完好无损。
ex.enText: This bowl has been preserved intact.

ex.chText: 这座建于15世纪的宅第保存完好。
ex.enText: The house from 15th century has been perfectly preserved.

synonyms.bx: 指将某物完好地保存，通常用被动语态。

ex.chText: 她坚称法国菜是世界上最好的。
ex.enText: She asserted that French cooking is the best in the world.

ex.chText: 那位科学家断言月球上没有水。
ex.enText: The scientist asserted that there is no water on the moon.

synonyms.bx: 含较强的主观意味，指坚决而明确地表示某事真实无误。

ex.enText: He contended that it was true.

ex.chText: 我认为失业是当今最为严重的社会弊病。
ex.enText: I would contend that unemployment is the most serious social problem today.

synonyms.bx: 指声称某事属实，含有与他人进行争辩的意思。

ex.chText: 他坚称自己曾看见过飞碟。
ex.enText: He maintains that he once saw a UFO.

synonyms.bx: 指坚决维护某种主张或观点等。

example: The pianist kept time with the metronome
keep count
I cannot keep track of all my employees
The appellate court upheld the verdict
He maintained his innocence
keep a diary
maintain a record
keep notes
She alone sustained her family
The money will sustain our good cause
There's little to earn and many to keep
I keep a car in the countryside
She keeps an apartment in Paris for her shopping trips
wield power and authority

tr: keep in safety and protect from harm, decay, loss, or destruction
example: We preserve these archeological findings
The old lady could not keep up the building
children must be taught to conserve our national heritage
The museum curator conserved the ancient manuscripts

tr: keep in a certain state, position, or activity
example: hold in place
She always held herself as a lady
The students keep me on my toes

value.def: If you maintain something, you continue to have it, and do not let it stop or grow weaker.

example.ex: The Department maintains many close contacts with the chemical industry...
example.tran: 这个部门与化工行业保持着众多密切的联系。

example.ex: Push yourself to make friends and to maintain the friendships.
example.tran: 要求自己与人交友并保持友谊。

example.ex: ...the emergency powers to try to maintain law and order.
example.tran: 维持法律秩序的应急权力

value.def: If you say that someone maintains that something is true, you mean that they have stated their opinion strongly but not everyone agrees with them or believes them.

example.ex: He has maintained that the money was donated for international purposes...
example.tran: 他坚称这笔捐款将用于国际用途。

example.ex: Prosecutors maintain no deal was made...
example.tran: 原告坚持说不存在任何交易。

example.ex: 'Not all feminism has to be like this,' Jo maintains...
example.tran: “女性主义不必全然如此，”乔断言。

example.ex: He had always maintained his innocence.
example.tran: 他始终坚称自己是无辜的。

value.def: If you maintain something at a particular rate or level, you keep it at that rate or level.

example.ex: The government was right to maintain interest rates at a high level.
example.tran: 政府维持高利率的做法是正确的。

example.ex: ...action is required to ensure standards are maintained at as high a level as possible.
example.tran: 要求采取行动确保标准维持在尽量高的水平上。

value.tran: 保持，维持（在某一比率或水平上）

value.def: If you maintain a road, building, vehicle, or machine, you keep it in good condition by regularly checking it and repairing it when necessary.

example.ex: ...a tough campaign to force authorities to maintain roads properly...
example.tran: 迫使当局妥善维修道路的艰难斗争

example.ex: The house costs a fortune to maintain...
example.tran: 维修这幢房子花销不菲。

example.ex: The cars are getting older and less well-maintained.
example.tran: 车越来越旧，保养得也越来越差。

value.def: If you maintain someone, you provide them with money and other things that they need.

example.ex: He should pay and maintain you as well.
example.tran: 他得给你钱，还得供养你。

example.ex: ...the basic costs of maintaining a child.
example.tran: 抚养一个孩子的基本费用

trans: （保持）处于…中；供养…使之以…生活

contain 包含，容纳 + er 表物 → 容器

con 加强 + tin 拿住 + ue → 从头拿到尾 → 继续
con 加强 + tin 拿住 + uous …的，continue的形容词 → 连续不断的

sus 下，后 + ten 拿住 + ance，sustain 的名词 → 粮食；支持
ten 拿住 + able 能…的 → 能拿住的 → 可守住的
ten 拿住 + acious 有…性质的 → 拿住不放的 → 固执的
ten 拿住 + acity 表状态 → 固执；不屈不挠
ten 拿住 + ant 表人 → 拿〔钱〕租房之人 → 房客
ten 拿住 + ancy 表状况 → 租赁（期限）
ten 拿住 + ure 表结果 → 拿住 → 占有权
un 不 + tenable 可守住的 → 不可防守的
im 向内 + man 逗留 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 留在内部的 → 内在的
